sects over custody of the holy sites 
rights of worship and maintenance are spelled out in minute 
detail in a set of rules dating back to the 1850s however 
jurisdiction over the roof of the church of the nativity is not 
specifically mentioned in the rules 
in the past area authorities the ottomans the british the 
jordanians and finally the israelis fixed the roof periodically 
to prevent squabbles among the sects 
but this year the greek orthodox church insisted on fixing the 
