countrys republics increasingly are disregarding kremlin 
authority the resolution said provisional agreements with the 
republics would help stabilize the social and economic situation 
in the country 
so far each republic has acted independently in introducing 
reforms to switch to a free market economy all but one of the 
countrys republics have declared sovereignty from the kremlin 
the result has been what many call a paralysis of power that 
has hindered any reform and caused a breakdown of the countrys 
political and economic life 
the supreme soviet said in its resolution that agreements should 
be reached with the republics to stop legal contradictions in 
their drives for sovereignty or outright independence the 
republics have passed laws that ignore or even contradict national 
legislation 
