off workers state governments also have trimmed their payrolls 
including massachusetts where up to 10000 part and fulltime 
state jobs have been eliminated over the past two years 
the surveys found that job losses by both public and private 
employers are adding to state spending as unemployed workers sign 
up for state benefits and more families join the welfare rolls 
