between his socialists and the opposition on how to turn around the 
moribund economy and end bulgarias political paralysis 
the noconfidence motion was defeated 201159 in secret 
balloting in the 400seat grand national assembly it came a day 
after lawmakers approved lukanovs austerity budget in a vote 
boycotted by the opposition lukanov had threatened to resign if 
the budget had failed to pass 
krastyu petkov head of the independent labor federation 
appealed to president zhelyu zhelev to call new elections he told 
state television a nonpolitial government of experts should run 
the country in the interim 
a smaller trade union has called a general strike starting 
monday if lukanov does not step down before then but the general 
prosecutor issued a statement friday warning that strikes based 
solely on political demands were not permitted 
prior to the vote lukanov defended himself against charges by 
the opposition that his government was ineffective and called for 
dialogue and honest compromise 
the socialists formerly the communist party won june elections 
and have 210 of the 400 seats in parliament but because some of 
those seats are held by renegades lukanov has not been able to 
count on a majority 
scarce supplies of food and consumer goods have fired anger 
among bulgarias frustrated citizens about the economic crisis and 
the political deadlock 
opposition leaders claim they would triumph in new elections 
and that bulgaria would win more international aid under an 
oppositionled government than one of former communists but 
lukanov said international aid does not depend on the color of 
the government 
the premier who returned to sofia on thursday from a 34nation 
paris summit said talks with other leaders convinced him no one 
would help a country in which there is no stability in which the 
reforms are not decisively implemented 
the opposition has repeatedly rejected lukanovs requests to 
join a broad socialistled coalition government insisting instead 
on naming the premier and holding key ministries 
</TEXT>
