bulldozers were clearing the rubble of 15 years of civil war 
during which the track because of its location right on beiruts 
dividing green line was caught in christianmoslem crossfire 
the track called the palace of peace was closed and reopened 
more than a dozen times during the civil war the last closure was 
in march 1989 during a rebellion by renegade gen michel aoun 
now peace finally seems to be coming to this nation of roughly 
35 million people 
of the 700 racing arabians in the stables at the track 400 
survived shelling duels between troops loyal to aoun and regulars 
