<TEXT>
marc eisenson has an important message for 
americans do yourself your country and your grandchildren a big 
favor and pay a few more dollars on your monthly bills make it a 
habit 
the withering industrial base the federal deficit the savings 
and loan crisis and even saddam husseins invasion of kuwait make 
it more imperative than ever that americans get out of debt 
eisenson says 
it just makes it clear that future stability is not assured 
eisenson said of world events if i am out of debt i can weather 
a lot of storms 
americans owe 24 trillion in mortgage debt and another 729 
billion in consumer credit bills federal reserve figures show 
ironically those big mortgages provide many people with their 
greatest opportunity to save money 
according to eisenson no investment not treasury bonds not 
the stock market is more lucrative in the long run than simply 
spending money to retire debts that allows people to avoid 
interest payments that run around 20 percent on many credit cards 
if you were to bring your balance down its like earning 20 
percent with your money said eisenson twenty percent is more 
than donald trump can earn safely it is absolutely guaranteed 
riskfree and it is available to only those who are unfortunately 
or fortunately in debt 
eisenson calls his system debt management and insists it holds 
the key to happiness and financial security for millions of 
americans 
the concept is especially effective when applied to longterm 
debt such as mortgages paying a few dollars extra a month can 
take thousands of dollars and years off a typical mortgage 
at 10 percent a 75000 mortgage takes 30 years to pay and 
winds up costing the borrower a total of 237000 
by paying just 25 a month extra a person can save 34000 and 
take five years off the mortgage according to eisensons formula 
pay 100 a month extra and save 78000 and 12 years off the same 
mortgage 
get in the habit of debt management i dont care how strapped 
you are you can pay some money even an extra five or 10 
dollars said eisenson you can start the process to free 
yourself of debt with very little money the kind of money 
everybody has got 
eisenson said he learned his debtfree values from his parents 
who lived fairly simple lives his brother taught him how to apply 
those values to mortgages and he paid off a 30year mortgage in 
five years at age 27 a former electrical engineer eisenson 47 
has devoted the last fifteen years to developing his debt 
management system 
that system is spelled out in the bankers secret a 233page 
book published this year by villard books a division of random 
house before the book eisenson delivered his message through a 
constantly evolving booklet 
along with his partner nancy castleman eisenson has also 
developed a computer program to allow consumers to tailor 
prepayment plans to their individual needs 
were zealots we want to change the world we want to reach 
every homeowner in america with our message its just crazy to 
give 34000 or more to a bank when you could use that money to put 
kids through college or finance your retirement said castleman 
how many homeowners are there in this country with mortgages 
thats how many people we want to reach 
too many americans do not understand the mechanics of debt and 
how easily they can avoid thousands of dollars in interest by 
paying more than the minimum each month eisenson said 
most people just dont understand it is something they can 
really use eisenson said without making any significant 
change in the short term without going without people can 
dramatically change their lives in the long term 
lately people are more receptive to his message 
people are no longer in the spend generation he said 
many are in financial trouble or on the edge of it a lot of 
people really do begin to prepay and it makes a significant 
difference in their lives 
 
