in holidaydampened activity volume on the big board averaged 
12653 million shares a day down from 16355 million the week 
before 
to some observers such as the economists s jay levy and david 
levy in chappaqua ny it wont be easy to get us business 
growing vigorously again even on the far side of the recession 
the excesses of the 1980s are being paid for in the 1990s 
the levys declare a decades profligacy cannot be overcome 
quickly 
says barbera we completely agree with the idea that the 
30year debt cycle is ending and that attitudes about borrowing and 
lending are going through a metamorphosis 
but we are also confident that at some point interest rate 
declines will rekindle both borrowing and building before recession 
turns into depression 
debts demise promises an end to the artificially high real 
shortterm interest rates witnessed in the 1980s he concludes 
longterm financial assets stocks and bonds will thrive in an 
environment of sharply lower rates 
