<DOCNO> AP901123-0157 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
yugoslavias largest pharmaceutical 
company agreed to merge with californiabased spi pharmaceuticals 
inc in one of the biggest eastwest transactions in yugoslavia 
since world war ii spi officials said 
under the agreement announced thursday in belgrade the assets 
of galenika pharmaceuticals would be transferred to a new joint 
company called icn galenika 
the combined company is expected to have annual sales of 370 
million 
spi will own 75 percent of the new company and galenika will own 
the remaining 25 percent according to company officials spi is 
based in costa mesa and is an 89 percentowned subsidiary of icn 
pharmaceuticals inc 
the transaction will provide galenika with capital to modernize 
equipment and improve its international marketing position the 
company said 
galenika is the largest manufacturer of pharmaceutical and 
chemical products in yugoslavia and serves markets throughout 
eastern europe and the soviet union 
owned by the yugoslavian government galenika will do an 
estimated 230 million in sales this year and employs 5800 
workers 
spi has estimated 1990 sales of 140 million 
we expect significant marketing synergies to occur from the 
consolidation of our businesses said milan panic chairman and 
chief executive officer of spi and its parent icn pharmaceuticals 
inc 
the merger agreement is subject to final approval by the federal 
secretariat for external economic relations of yugoslavia and the 
boards of spi its parent and galenika 
the consolidation was made possible by changes in yugoslavian 
law in late 1988 permitting privatization of governmentowned 
businesses spi said 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

