lloyds bank plc said friday it has cut 2000 staff 
this year as part of an ongoing review of its banking operations 
the cuts came mostly through natural attrition and early 
retirement throughout the company including head office staff it 
said 
lloyds one of britains largest commercial banks currently 
employs 55000 
further job cuts are expected in the future but the exact 
numbers havent been decided said a spokesman who wasnt 
identified in keeping with bank practice 
other british banks also have been trimming staff and 
consolidating branch networks in a bid to reduce operating costs 
and bolster profitability 
