<TEXT>
the government on friday renewed its decree for a 
capital gains tax an issue which helped provoke a stock traders 
strike earlier this week but postponed implementation for two 
months 
the cabinets action put off possible implementation of the tax 
until feb 15 it had to renew the decree because without action 
the decree would have expired following parliaments failure to 
approve it within the mandatory twomonth limit 
the capital gains tax applies to small investors companies and 
institutional investors already have to include capital gains on 
stock trading in their corporate earnings but individual investors 
arent required to include capital gains on their income tax 
filings 
italian stock markets reopened thursday following a fourday 
strike by floor traders 
the floor traders opposed the proposed changes in the capital 
gains tax because of the complicated way the tax would have been 
collected and the much higher tax rate 
the traders have also been protesting the governments slowness 
in implementing longawaited reforms expected to make the italian 
market more competitive internationally the reforms concern 
regulating public tender offers securities trading companies and 
insider trading 
</TEXT>
