<TEXT>
ameritrust corp expecting a loss for the 
year announced friday it had halved the dividend on the banking 
companys common stock 
officials said they resorted to the cut the first in the 
companys 96year history mainly because of problem loans linked 
to a lagging commercial real estate market 
the ameritrust board of directors declared a quarterly dividend 
of 16 cents per common share down from 32 cents per share in the 
third quarter the dividend is payable dec 10 to stockholders of 
record dec 3 
the boards decision to reduce the dividend on the common 
stock was prudent in view of our expectations for financial 
performance in the nearterm and general economic conditions 
said craig r smith chairman and chief executive of ameritrust 
for the first nine months of 1990 ameritrust reported a loss of 
19 million smith did not say how large the fourthquarter loss 
was expected to be 
ameritrust spokeswoman terry taylor said smiths recommendation 
to cut the dividend was prompted by the size of this years loss 
and was a part of an overall effort to cut costs 
ameritrust has more than 200 commercial banking offices in ohio 
indiana and michigan and a major trust subsidiary in dallas 
</TEXT>
