<TEXT>
francis buddy kemp president of ncnb corp 
died of brain cancer early friday at his home he was 50 
kemp had been chairman of ncnb texas since july 1988 when the 
charlotte nc banking company expanded into the state he had 
suffered from brain cancer for more than a year 
we feel his absence intensely said ncnb chairman hugh 
mccoll in a statement we have lost someone who is very special 
to us 
kemp a native of reidsville nc joined ncnb in 1967 as a 
credit analyst and quickly advanced in the company by 1972 he was 
a senior vice president and national division executive 
kemp was promoted to executive vice president in 1975 took over 
the north carolina banking group in 1977 and became president of 
ncnb corp in october 1985 
he relinquished his daytoday responsibilities at ncnb in 
november 1989 after undergoing brain surgery 
kemp is survived by his wife ginger their children frank and 
elizabeth and by a brother david kemp of reidsville 
the funeral service will be at myers park presbyterian church in 
charlotte on monday with a memorial service at the first 
presbyterian church in dallas 
