consumers began a christmas shopping season that many retailers 
fear will be their worst in years due to the twin grinches of a 
weak economy and the persian gulf crisis 
in keeping with a tradition thats as much a part of 
thanksgiving weekend as leftover turkey shoppers queued early on 
friday some standing outside in the rain before stores and malls 
opened 
by midmorning many an aisle was crowded from midtown 
manhattans swank department stores to the state street mall in 
chicago to the shops that ring san franciscos union square but 
many of the shoppers were only browsing not buying 
 
washington ap the federal government opened fiscal 1991 with 
a 315 billion deficit in october the first month of what is 
expected to be a record year for red ink the treasury department 
said 
the budget gap was 21 percent higher than the 261 billion 
deficit of october 1989 the increase reflects the buildup of us 
forces in the persian gulf and the escalation of the savings and 
loan bailout officials said friday 
 
new york ap the new york stock exchange halted trading for 
more than 90 minutes because of a power disruption at the nations 
largest stock market 
the disruption friday which nyse officials called the first in 
recent memory shut down the exchange at 941 am est 11 minutes 
into the start of trading nyse spokesman richard torrenzano said 
the problem was powerrelated but that the exchange hadnt 
identified its exact cause 
 
